                        <p>We repair all major brands of mobile phones, smartphones, smartwatches, and various types of traditional watches. If you're unsure about a specific device, please don't hesitate to call us!</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item animated-item">
                    <button class="accordion-header">How long does a typical repair take?</button>
                    <div class="accordion-content">
                        <p>Most common repairs, like screen replacements and battery changes, can be completed within a few hours, often on the same day. More complex issues might require more time, but we'll provide an accurate estimated timeframe upon diagnosis.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item animated-item">
                    <button class="accordion-header">Do you use genuine parts?</button>
                    <div class="accordion-content">
                        <p>Yes, we prioritize using genuine or OEM (Original Equipment Manufacturer) quality parts for all repairs to ensure durability, optimal performance, and your satisfaction.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item animated-item">
                    <button class="accordion-header">Do you offer warranty on repairs?</button>
                    <div class="accordion-content">
                        <p>Absolutely! We stand by the quality of our work and offer a warranty on our repair services. The specific duration depends on the type of repair and part used. Please ask our staff for detailed warranty information.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item animated-item">
                    <button class="accordion-header">Can I get a quote before the repair?</button>
                    <div class="accordion-content">
                        <p>Certainly! We offer free diagnostics and will provide you with a transparent, no-obligation quote before proceeding with any repair work. There are no hidden charges.</p>
